author: Huawei
description:
#Huawei celebrated 25 years in Egypt at the Grand Egyptian Museum, joined by senior government officials, industry leaders, partners, and Huawei executives from across the region. The iconic venue symbolized the fusion of Egypt’s rich past with its digital future, underscoring Huawei’s role in advancing the nation’s ICT ecosystem.

Huawei reaffirmed its vision for Egypt’s future, built on the principles of new value, new infrastructure, and new ecosystem. The company pledged continued support for initiatives in inclusive connectivity, education, government services, security, and energy.

The event was led by H.E. Dr. Amr Talaat, Minister of Communications and Information Technology, and Egyptian officials, and featured Benjamin Hou, CEO of Huawei Egypt, who reiterated Huawei’s “In Egypt, For Egypt” commitment to accelerate Vision 2030 and build an intelligent, connected, and inclusive digital future. Read more: https://bit.ly/4qQCxlu #HuaweiEgypt #Vision2030 #ThisIsHuawei
title: Huawei in Egypt: 25 Years of Innovation and Partnership
